{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01JzQagJcYHDbhLPL5EKiuXP","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The task is complete. `output/calculation_note.md` exists and, backed by first-principles working files, reports all six required quantities with assumptions and confidence levels.\n\n## What was built\n\nA coupled physics model of the passive RCCS natural-circulation loop, all from the sanctioned inputs + cited textbook correlations (no facility data consulted):\n\n- **`airprops.py`** — air properties (ideal-gas ρ, Sutherland μ/k, standard cₚ), validated against tables.\n- **`rccs_model.py`** — steady solver: buoyancy stack-head vs friction/form losses → flow; energy balance → ΔT; Gnielinski internal convection → wall temp; gray-radiation network + enclosed-cavity convection → plate temp and rad/conv split.\n- **`accident_transient.py`** — lumped-capacitance transient with quasi-steady flow and Q_removed(T_plate) feedback.\n- **`weather_sweep.py`** — outdoor-T and wind parametric sweeps.\n- **`fig_transient.png`, `fig_weather.png`, `transient_trace.csv`** — results.\n\n## Headline answers (baseline, 56 kW)\n\n1. **Mass flow** ≈ 0.55 kg/s (33 kg/min) — Medium\n2. **Riser air ΔT** ≈ 100 °C — Medium\n3. **Riser wall** ≈ 135 °C (z=3500, hot face); **plate** ≈ 360 °C — Medium(-high)\n4. **Split** ≈ 90 % radiation / 10 % convection — High (direction)\n5. **Accident:** peak plate ≈ 361 °C at t≈85 h; **levels off, no runaway** (radiation ∝T⁴ + buoyancy give strong negative feedback), stays ≪540 °C steel limit → **safe** — High\n6. **Weather:** flow varies only ±8 % over −18…+24 °C; wind is stronger (±20 % at 11 m/s) — High direction\n\nThe note ranks the **most uncertain assumption** as the heat actually delivered to the risers (56 vs ~70 kW), bracketed by a sensitivity case, followed by riser loss coefficients and the assumed riser emissivity. It contains an explicit provenance statement that all numbers were derived from physics and the given inputs without looking up the facility's data."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":525,"cache_read_input_tokens":94344,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":525},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"global"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6fa864fa-613d-4ef1-baa7-f2191f1aaf7b","uuid":"fa5c5b6e-6238-4a21-8b07-966726265c11","request_id":"req_011Ccc6htTAd3oK3B8zahTp8"}
